---
Description: Buddhist saying
Source:
  ID: 57c5499b-c3b2-4b09-92a9-a6e977a32050
  Locus:
    Page: 137
    Verse: 13
Tags:
  - Evil
---
The man who has no wound on his hand may touch poison with his hand, for
poison cannot affect a man with no open wound. Neither is there evil for
the man free of evil.
